:bulb: *Super query mode for very complex queries*
Multidoc/multistep is running for a very long time (15m+) when I execute a very complex query. Is this expected? For an insanely great response, it may even be ok to wait but just trying to understand the expectation (almost wonder if we setup a different mode for this which is intentionally more async). What's surprising is that I don't see any new steps being generated in multistep as I wait too.
• Chatbot link - https://aihub.instabase.com/hub/apps/a1546a31-555d-4d9e-bdb4-b5ad55219ebc
• Query in above snippet

I'm trying to recreate a "super complex task" v/s simply asking "can I underwrite properties in Iran". It feels like the user persona here would actually be willing to wait for amazing results too. For instance, see how Devin handles something like this - takes 40min! to come back, sadly we can't try it so don't know how good the response is.
